
# üéÆ AI Learning Plan: Build a Tetris Bot

## üìç Phase 1: Core Foundations (2‚Äì4 weeks)
**Goal**: Build essential math and Python skills for AI.

- **Topics**:
  - Linear algebra (vectors, matrices)
  - Probability & statistics
  - Python for data science (NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib)

- **Resources**:
  - Khan Academy: https://www.khanacademy.org/math/linear-algebra
  - 3Blue1Brown YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZHQObOWTQDMsr9K-rj53DwVRMYO3t5Yr
  - Python Data Science Handbook: https://jakevdp.github.io/PythonDataScienceHandbook/

- **Mini Project**: Analyze a dataset from https://www.kaggle.com/datasets (e.g., Titanic survival prediction)

---

## üìç Phase 2: Machine Learning Basics (4‚Äì6 weeks)
**Goal**: Understand and implement classic ML algorithms.

- **Topics**:
  - Supervised learning (regression, classification)
  - Unsupervised learning (clustering, dimensionality reduction)
  - Model evaluation (confusion matrix, ROC, F1)

- **Resources**:
  - Coursera ML Course: https://www.coursera.org/learn/machine-learning
  - Hands-On ML Book: https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/hands-on-machine-learning/9781492032632/

- **Mini Project**: Build a spam email classifier or a movie recommendation system.

---

## üìç Phase 3: Deep Learning (4‚Äì8 weeks)
**Goal**: Learn how neural networks work and build deep models.

- **Topics**:
  - Neural networks (forward/backpropagation)
  - CNNs for image data
  - RNNs/LSTMs for sequences
  - Transfer learning

- **Resources**:
  - Deep Learning Specialization: https://www.coursera.org/specializations/deep-learning
  - Fast.ai Course: https://course.fast.ai/
  - PyTorch Tutorials: https://pytorch.org/tutorials/

- **Mini Project**: Image classifier (e.g., cats vs. dogs), or sentiment analysis on tweets.

---

## üìç Phase 4: Real-World Projects & Portfolio (Ongoing)
**Goal**: Apply your skills to real problems and build a portfolio.

- **Ideas**:
  - AI-powered chatbot
  - Stock price predictor
  - Object detection app
  - AI art generator

- **Platforms**:
  - Kaggle: https://www.kaggle.com/competitions
  - GitHub: https://github.com/
  - Hugging Face: https://huggingface.co/

---

## üìç Phase 5: Advanced Topics (Optional)
**Goal**: Explore cutting-edge AI.

- **Topics**:
  - Transformers & LLMs (e.g., BERT, GPT)
  - Reinforcement learning
  - Generative models (GANs, VAEs)
  - AI ethics and fairness

- **Resources**:
  - Deep RL Nanodegree: https://www.udacity.com/course/deep-reinforcement-learning-nanodegree--nd893
  - Hugging Face Course: https://huggingface.co/course

